FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Everything you need to know about wrapping tokens on Ethereum
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Token wrapping is the process of converting one cryptocurrency token into another that's compatible with a different blockchain or protocol. In our app, we focus on wrapping tokens on the Ethereum network.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: Why would I want to wrap my tokens?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: Wrapping tokens allows you to use them in different DeFi protocols, gain additional functionality, or take advantage of lower transaction fees while maintaining the value of your original asset.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: How does the wrapping process work?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Our app provides a simple interface where you can connect your wallet, select the token you want to wrap, specify the amount, and confirm the transaction. The app then interacts with smart contracts to lock your original tokens and mint the wrapped version.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: Are there any fees for wrapping tokens?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: While our app doesn't charge any fees for the wrapping process itself, you'll need to pay the standard Ethereum network gas fees to execute the smart contract interactions.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: Can I unwrap my tokens later?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Absolutely! Our app also supports unwrapping, allowing you to convert your wrapped tokens back to their original form at any time, subject to the same network gas fees.

PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions about Token Wrapping
ACCORDION_QUESTION_1: What is token wrapping on Ethereum?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Token wrapping is the process of converting a cryptocurrency or token into an ERC-20 compatible token on the Ethereum network. This allows for improved interoperability and functionality within the Ethereum ecosystem.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: Why would I want to wrap my tokens?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: Wrapping tokens can provide benefits such as increased liquidity, compatibility with DeFi protocols, and access to additional features while maintaining the value of the original asset.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: Is it safe to wrap my tokens?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: Yes, when done through our secure app, token wrapping is safe. The original tokens are locked in a smart contract, and an equivalent amount of wrapped tokens is minted. You can always unwrap your tokens to retrieve the original asset.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Are there any fees for wrapping tokens?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: While our app doesn't charge additional fees for wrapping, you'll need to pay standard Ethereum network gas fees to execute the wrapping transaction. The exact cost varies based on network congestion.
